entry.title: [CodeHealth] Eliminate AcrossTasksDanglingUntriaged in CaptionBubble
entry.content:
In some tests in CaptionBubbleControllerViewsTest, tick_clock_ in

CaptionBubble will be overwritten with the task runner's mock clock via

set_tick_clock_for_testing. However, in these tests, the task runner

will be destructed earlier than CaptionBubbleControllerViews (which owns

CaptionBubble), and thus tick_clock_ will be a dangling ptr.



This CL inserts an explicit reset of tick_clock_ before the destruction

of the task runner to avoid this issue.



Bug: 1512655

entry.title: Add a screen-ai CIPD package for PDF OCR E2E tests on Linux
entry.content:
To have E2E tests for PDF OCR on Windows, macOS, and Linux, we need to

be able to download and use the screen-ai library in those tests.

Pursuing this goal, we upload the screen-ai library for Linux to CIPD

and download it from CIPD to //third_party/screen-ai. This downloaded

library is then loaded in E2E tests (i.e. browser tests).



For more information, visit go/chrome_screen_ai_tests and read the

Uploading the library files to CIPD section.

entry.title: Fenced frame: Add ad component remote context WPT support.
entry.content:
Introduces a way to embed ad components within frames and be able to run

arbitrary JavaScript in them.



Steps for setting up:

1. Create a fenced frame or URN iframe remote context using either

attachFencedFrameContext() or attachIFrameContext(). Specify the new

`include_component: true` parameter when calling the function. This

will create a remote context URL/URN, but not actually create a frame.

2. To create the ad component frame, call either

attachComponentFencedFrameContext() or attachComponentIFrameContext().

This will construct an ad component frame, and return the remote context

object the same way that attachFencedFrameContext/attachIFrameContext

does. This can be interacted with in the same way that any other remote

context frame can be interacted with.



As a proof of concept, this CL makes the following test changes:

1. Updates `nested-opaque-ad-sizes.https.html` to finally be functional.

2. Adds a WPT to test that ad components can send automatic beacons with

a header opt-in.

There are currently cases where the browser process tells the renderer

process to navigate to empty URLs. Blink treats these as about:blank,

rather than sending a DidCommit IPC with an empty URL.



This CL updates NavigationSimulator to behave similarly, so that the

committed URL in unit tests is not empty. This is important for

upcoming navigation changes which are more strict, and would cause the browser to kill the renderer process for committing an empty URL,

instead of the current code that rewrites the empty URL in FilterURL to

about:blank#blocked.

entry.title: Simplify SingleFieldFormFillRouter
entry.content:
SingleFieldFormFillRouter currently holds WeakPtrs to the

AutocompleteHistoryManager, IbanManager and MerchantPromoCodeManager.



This is unnecessary, given the lifetimes of the four classes:

- AutocompleteHistoryManager, IbanManager and MerchantPromoCodeManager

are KeyedServices.

- SingleFieldFormFillRouter is owned by the BAM, which is per frame.



Even after we refactor the BAM to be per tab, the KeyedServices will

always outlive SingleFieldFormFillRouter.



As such, this CL:

- Removes the WeakPtrFactories from the AutocompleteHistoryManager,

IbanManager and MerchantPromoCodeManager.

- Makes the members in SingleFieldFormFillRouter raw_refs/raw_ptrs (the

AutocompleteHistoryManager always exists, but the other two are not

supported on some platforms).

- Removes an unnecessary null check.

- Cleans up the SingleFieldFormFillRouter tests a bit:

- Instead of having pointers to all relevant classes in the fixture,

just store the values.

- Reorder the members, so the destruction order matches reality.

entry.title: [dPWA] Remove web_app_prefs_utils
entry.content:
This CL moves all the free functions from web_app_prefs_utils into

WebAppPrefGuardrails with the correct visibility, to remove duplicate

code from persisting. As a result of this, the utils file can be

removed, so this CL also removes all includes of the header.



The only other change is the registration of the various web app

preferences, which are done now inside the WebAppProviderFactory and

other respective places, like WebAppPrefGuardrails for guardrails

and WebAppPolicyManager for policy based keys.



Future changes to improve things in this class, like using a single

entry.title: Ensure that AutofillPopupControllerImpl only observes a RFH once.
entry.content:
AutofillPopupControllerImpl should only register a single callback

for key press events at a time. However, the status quo does not

guarantee that: RenderWidgetHost::AddKeyPressEventCallback DCHECKs

that there are no duplicate callbacks, which compares callbacks by

equality comparison. Equality comparison of two RepeatingCallbacks

returns true if one is obtained by copying another, but false if the two

callbacks are created via separate BindRepeating calls (even if their

arguments match).



When Show() is called twice, it is therefore currently possible that

there are multiple KeyPressEventCallbacks by a single

AutofillPopupControllerImpl. The reason that this has not caused issues

in practice is likely that these callbacks have the ability to "capture"

an event - if an earlier callback returns "true", the subsequent

callbacks are not notified anymore. Only if the event is not handled

will all callbacks be notified.



This CL ensures that existing KeyPressEventCallbacks are removed

prior to adding a new one.

entry.title: [Privacy Sandbox] Gate attestation sentinel behind a feature flag.
entry.content:
This CL gates the sentinel guard behind a default enabled feature flag. This allows us to experiment turning off the sentinel via Finch.

Because the feature is default enabled so it does not change the

current behavior.



There are about 0.95% of Privacy Sandbox API calls on Android default-

allowed for the attestation checks because the parsing is finish

without an in-memory attestation map.



There are several possible causes for this:

1. The sentinel aborts the parsing.

2. Cannot create the sentinel file before parsing.

3. Cannot remove the sentinel file after parsing.

4. The parsing of protobuf encoded attestation list fails.



The histogram shows there are very few data points in the last 3

buckets. We suspect there might be problems elsewhere that caused the

sentinel file to be left on client's disk. We plan on turning this

feature off on Android via Finch experiment.

entry.title: Make html_element_lookup_trie check feature flags for elements most of the time.
entry.content:
This makes html_element_lookup_trie check feature flags when determining

whether to return HTMLTag::kSomeElementName or HTMLTag::kUnknown, unless

there are origin trials involved. This means that there is less risk of

breakage due to failure to properly condition HTML parser changes behind

a feature flag.



However when origin trials are involved the parser changes must still be

properly conditioned by a feature flag. Handling origin trials properly

requires passing a document or execution context to the tokenizer, which

is used by the HTMLPreloadScanner, which I believe would break threading

rules (although I haven't found documentation of those rules).

entry.content:
This CL uses ApplicationContext::GetApplicationLocale() instead of

[NSLocale currentLocale] to check that if browser state is eligible

for price alerts. This allows tests to pass as tests override the application context with a TestingApplicationContext.

is "en-US" and not "en_US":

The CL also changes the locale used in TestingApplicationContext to

be "en-US" to match the locale format in the real Chrome application.
